<HEADLINE> Xinhua World New Summary at 16:00 GMT, February 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India and Cyprus Tuesday decided to improve the
shipping links between the two countries by signing an agreement
on maritime transport which is expected to further strengthen
bilateral economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French Foreign Minister Herve de Charette will attend
the inter-ministerial meeting between the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) and the European Union (EU), to be held in
Singapore from February 13 to 15.
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- Palestinian President Yasser Arafat said Tuesday
that the coming steps toward settling the Palestinian issue depend
on how the joint committees formed with Israel will work to
examine all the outstanding issues.
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- The Philippines and the United States have agreed to
cancel their joint military exercises scheduled for this year,
Philippine Armed Forces Chief of Staff Arnulfo Acedera said
Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
