<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Being Recovered From His Illness, Says Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris
Yeltsin is recovering from a bout with double pneumonia that
hospitalized him in early January.
</P>
<P>
Presidential spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky today told a news
briefing that although the president is recovering, "one should
not expect his hurried return" to the Kremlin.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Yeltsin's physicians "are twice more
cautious" about the health of the president, who had returned to
the Kremlin just over two weeks ago after a six-month absence from
a heart ailment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
