<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tajikstan Began Negotiation on Releasing Hostages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Earlier, a special commission headed by Tajik vice-premier
Abdurakhmon Azimov had been instructed to work out a mechanism on
exchanging the hostages for 40 supporters of the Sodirov brothers.
</P>
<P>
The current hostages crisis started early this month when a
group commanded by the Rizvon Sadirov captured four employees of
the United Nations Refugee Agency (UNHCR) and four Russian
reporters.
</P>
<P>
The kidnappers, who had released some of the hostages from the
UN, are demanding free passage for colleagues based in neighboring
Afghanistan to return to Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
The hostages, among them the Tajikstan security minister,
Saidamir Ziljirpv, who was sent to negotiate early this month, are
being held by Bakhrom Sadirov's group in the area of Kalainav, 80
kilometers east of Dushanbe, the Tajik capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
