<HEADLINE> Urgent: UN, Itar-Tass Hostages Released by Tajik Opposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, February 11 (Xinhua) -- U.N. military mission observer
Major G. Hoenig of Austria, held as a hostage by the Tajik
opposition, has been released and brought to Dushanbe, capital of
Tajikistan, the Itar-Tass news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. military mission sources were quoted as saying that
Hoenig was seized by the opposition troops of Bakhrom Sodirov on
February 4 when he was being taken away from Garm.
</P>
<P>
The sources said U.N. mission physicians have begun health
check for Hoenig.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Itar-Tass correspondent Galina Gridneva has sent
may-day message for mass media from Sodirov's base in Kalainav in
eastern Tajikistan after being released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
