<DOCNO> XIE19970212.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Launches Air Raids Against Guerrillas in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Israeli warplanes carried out
this afternoon a series of air raids on guerrilla targets in the
Hezbollah-controlled Beqaa Valley in eastern Lebanon, reportedly
wounding seven people.
</P>
<P>
Security sources said that four Israeli jet fighters, covered
by six other warplanes, launched an air offensive at targets on
the outskirts of the Shiite Muslim stronghold of Baalbek city
in eastern Lebanon at 1:15 p.m. (1115 GMT).
</P>
<P>
The Israeli warplanes fired four air-to-surface missiles in
the direction of a radio station of the pro-Iranian Hezbollah,
or Party of God, on a hill and badly damaged the building.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses in Baalbek said that they saw black smokes rising
into the sky from the hilltop and covered the area, and
explosions echoed across the city.
</P>
<P>
Security sources said, on a condition of anonymity, that
at least four people were wounded in the air raid.
</P>
<P>
A group of people in Hezbollah's black uniforms set up
blockades around the hill and preventing reporters and others
from approaching, and ambulances were witnessed rushing to the
scene.
</P>
<P>
The fundamentalist Hezbollah, which spearheads a guerrilla
warfare against the Israeli occupation in south Lebanon, denied
that any of its members were wounded by the Israeli warplanes.
</P>
<P>
This was the fourth air raid by the Israeli air force at the
"Sawt Mutabasin" radio since November 1992.
</P>
<P>
The radio resumed transmission one hour after the attack.
</P>
<P>
In another air raid, Israeli warplanes attacked a base of a
radical Palestinian organization only five kilometers west of the
Syrian-Lebanese border, injuring three Palestinian guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Local security sources said that two Israeli helicopters
carried out the attack on a base of the Popular Front for the
Liberation of Palestinian (PFLP) at Yagoub in western Beqaa and
wounded three members of the organization.
</P>
<P>
The security sources also reported that Israeli helicopters
fired missiles at a base of the PFLP at Naameh in western Beqaa,
without causing casualties.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli army spokesman announced in Jerusalem that Israeli
warplanes launched two air strikes on targets in western Beqaa
in southeast Lebanon "not far away from the Syrian border."
</P>
<P>
The air strikes came two days after Hezbollah guerrillas
ambushed an Israeli patrol in the Israeli self-proclaimed
"security zone" in south Lebanon, injuring seven Israeli
soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Hit-and-run attacks by Muslim guerrillas and bombardments by
Israeli forces constitute a daily scene on the last active
battle front of the Arab-Israeli conflict.
</P>
<P>
Israel established the 1,100-square-kilometer "security zone"
in south Lebanon in 1985 in a bid to protect northern Israel from
cross-border attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
