<HEADLINE> Government Troops Kill 40 Rebels in Western </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan government troops
killed 40 rebels in a fierce battle in Kyambura, western
Uganda, in the last three days, army sources said yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Three soldiers of the governemnt troops were wounded in the
battle, they added.
</P>
<P>
Local residents told the New Vision newspaper that about 120
rebels of the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) hided in Kyambura of
western Bushenyi District yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The sources told the newspaper that they are still pursuing the
remnants of the rebel forces.
</P>
<P>
