<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> COMESA Clearing House Under Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The clearing house of the
Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA) is under
restructuring in line with international trade developments, an
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Davison Marape, acting executive secretary of the clearing
house, said the changes would include the introduction of a new
payment system in April.
</P>
<P>
He said a unit of account for payment of trade transactions
would be introduced by member states through the clearing house
based on the U.S. Dollar as opposed to the current arrangement
based on the Special Drawing Rights (SDR) of the International
Monetary Fund.
</P>
<P>
The system would automatically introduce a flexible exchange
rate system and replace the rigid system currently in place, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The official added that the clearing house was also
undertaking an aggressive education campaign to the business
community, banks and government institutions to popularize the
system in all sectors of the economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
