<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Takes Measures Against AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe will this year import
five million male condoms and 420,000 female condoms for public
distribution as it intensifies preventive and control measures
against AIDS.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Zimbabwe's National AIDS Coordination
Programme Coordinator, Everisto Marowa, at a one-day consultative
meeting on HIV/AIDS held in capital Harare today.
</P>
<P>
"In response to the need to make the female condom available,
the drugs control council has agreed to the importation of this
device," said Marowa.
</P>
<P>
"Logistics for importation of the condoms are being worked
out," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Zimbabwean government approved the use of the female
condom last year following pressure from women's groups.
</P>
<P>
A recent report on female condom from the World Health
Organisation (WHO) said research work indicated that the condom
had no side effects and did not cause genital lesions.
</P>
<P>
The consultative meeting was attended by over 200 people from
international donor agencies, non-governmental organizations and
government officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
