<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Commander of the Lesotho
Defense Force, Makhula Mosakeng, today warned renegade policemen
against taking any further action to pose a threat to stability
of the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here today from Lesotho's capital of Maseru
quoted Mosakeng as saying that the army will play an important
role to end a week-long police mutiny.
</P>
