<HEADLINE> Manchester Gets 43 Mln Pounds to Rebuild Bombed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
London, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The British government
announced Monday that it will contribute 43 million pounds (70.5
million US dollars) to the cost of rebuilding the city center of
Manchester which was devastated by an IRA bomb last June.
</P>
<P>
The grant, announced by Deputy Prime Minister Michael
Heseltine, is in addition to 20 million pounds (32.8 million US
dollars) of European Union funds already committed to the
rebuilding and will be spent by Manchester Millennium, the task
force set up to oversee the rebuilding, on infrastructure
projects.
</P>
<P>
Work is expected to start soon on the city redevelopment scheme
designed by consultants EDAW and selected after an urban design
competition.
</P>
