<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- The Supreme Court of Zambia
today dismissed an opposition application challenging the
qualification of President Frederick Chiluba to contest the
presidential elections held last November.
</P>
<P>
Chief Justice Matthew Ngulube, sitting with other six supreme
court judges, made the ruling here today.
</P>
<P>
Five opposition parties are challenging Chiluba's nationality
for the presidential candidature, claiming that Chiluba's father
is a Zairean.
</P>
