Party, Agenda for Zambia, the National Congress Party and the
United National Independence Party (UNIP) led by former president
Kenneth Kaunda.
</P>
<P>
Under the new constitution signed by Chiluba, those whose
parents are foreign immigrants cannot contest the presidency.
</P>
<P>
The UNIP and some other opposition parties boycotted the
elections held under the constitution, which factually barred
Kaunda from running for the presidency because his parents are
Malawian immigrants. 
