<HEADLINE> Donation from Doctors Saves Poor Girl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A girl who could not afford
medical treatment has regained her health thanks to donations
from her doctors.
</P>
<P>
About a month ago Fang Yuxiu, a farmer's daughter in
northwest China's Gansu province, was sent to the Provincial
People's Hospital for treatment for heart disease.
</P>
<P>
To save the girl an operation costing at least 8,000 yuan
(nearly 1,000 US dollars) was necessary.
</P>
<P>
This was far beyond what the family, living in Jishishan
county, the poorest county of Gansu, could afford. So, the doctors
contributed the money between them and the operation was performed
promptly and smoothly.
</P>
<P>
"My life was saved by these warmhearted doctors, and they have
taught me how to care for and love others," said Fang, tearfully,
when she left the hospital on the eve of the traditional spring
festival. 
</P>
