there were many parts which were not conveyed to the families of
the hostages."
</P>
<P>
The first round of the so-called preliminary dialogue took
place Tuesday for about four hours at a private home across from
the diplomatic compound in Lima.
</P>
<P>
The face-to-face talks between Peruvian Education Minister
Domingo Palermo and Roli Rojas, the No.2 man among the rebels
inside the residence, were aimed at finding a peaceful end to the
58-day-old standoff.
</P>
<P>
They reportedly adopted procedures for future dialogue and
agreed to continue talking in accordance with a schedule to be
agreed upon later.
</P>
<P>
The rebels of the Tupac Amaru Revolutionary Movement seized the
Japanese ambassador's residence on December 17, taking hundreds of
hostages. Most of them were released later but the 72 people are
still held captive. 
