<HEADLINE> EU Approves Open Competition for Portugal Telecom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission
approved a timetable today to open up to full competition
Portugal's telecommunications from January 1, 2000.
</P>
<P>
According to the timetable, which was made at the request of
the Portugese government, voice telephones will be completely
deregulated from that date. In the meantime, direct international
connections for GSM mobile phone providers would be opened to free
competition from January 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
As for infrastructures, the opportunity would be given for
competitors to enter the Portuguese market from the middle of this
year.
</P>
<P>
Alternative infrastructure providers for already deregulated
services would be permitted from July 1 of 1997 and Portugal must
liberalize without delay the market for GSM mobile phone
alternative infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
However, under the derestrictive directives of the European
Union, Portugal is entitled to request a derogation period up to
2003. 
</P>
</TEXT>
