<HEADLINE> China's Labor Force to Reach Peak in 2016 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The coming 30 years will
see the biggest labor force ever in China, the current issue of
the Beijing-based "China Information" reported.
</P>
<P>
The number of workers will reach a peak of 870 million by the
year 2016.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the combined number of students at universities, and
secondary and primary schools will climb to 300 million by the
year 2030, the paper quoted statistics released by the State
Statistics Bureau, as revealing.
</P>
<P>
The working-age population will remain above 800 million
between 2003 and 2032, according to the statistical forecast.
</P>
<P>
Despite the abundant supply of labor, the paper stated, the
coming three decades will see a deficiency in funds and per-capita
share of resources as well as increased pressure from unemployment.
 
</P>
