<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-12 14:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani Rejects German Intervention in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Hashemi
Rafsanjani today rejected German intervention in the arrest of the
chief editor of an Iranian magazine, who sought political asylum
in Sweden and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani told a press conference here today that Faraj
Sarkohi's case is a domestic issue by a hundred percent and
"Germany should not interfere in it."
</P>
<P>
On Iran's stand vis-a-vis German government's reaction to the
case of Sarkohi, he noted, "From our point of view this is
ambiguous and a cause of surprise."
</P>
<P>
"Sarkohi had been in Germany and the Germans declined to
tell everything, thus the case has turned to a hue and cry
and a puzzle," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said "What is important is the reason behind the issue
and other things are not of parallel importance."
</P>
<P>
Iranian security authorities said that the chief editor of the
Persian weekly Adineh was arrested along with his brother and two
other smugglers while attempting to make an illegal exit in
Bushehr, a port city in southern Iran last week.
</P>
<P>
Ismaiel Sarkohi, the brother of the Iranian writer, said last
week that Faraj Sarkohi is mentally unstable.
</P>
<P>
Mahmoud Mohammadi, spokesman of Iran's Foreign Ministry, has
said that the case of Faraj Sarkohi was unrelated to relations
between Iran and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Since Sarkohi's arrest last week, Sweden and Germany have been
trying to find out what has happened to the Iranian journalist who
has disappeared twice in three months.
</P>
<P>
On November 3, 1996 Sarkohi disappeared after he entered
Tehran International airport. The authorities in Tehran maintained
that Sarkohi had boarded a plane to Germany. On December 20,
Sarkohi reappeared, saying that he had been in Germany, trying to
resolve a family dispute with his wife who resides in Germany.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, Swedish Foreign Minister Pierre Schori in
Stockholm called on the Iranian government to clarify what has
happened to Sarkohi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
