<HEADLINE> 43 PKK Rebels Killed in Turkey's Cross-Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- some 43 rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in three cross-border
air operations against PKK camps in northern Iraq staged by
Turkish air forces in January, the semi-official Anatolia News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that Turkish F-16 and F-4 fighters took
off from Diyarbakir air base and Erhac air base in Malatya
and bombarded the PKK camps in Meina and Zap regions in
northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Many PKK camps were destroyed in the two regions of
northern Iraq and 23 PKK militants were wiped out in Gulka
region and 20 in Nazur region in the cross-border air
operations, said the report.
</P>
<P>
More than 21,000 people including PKK rebels, civilians and
government troops have been killed since August 1984 when the
PKK started fighting for self-rule in southeastern Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
