<HEADLINE> Spring Festival Boosts Retail Sales in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The outgoing Spring
Festival, which fell on February 7 this year, has brought brisk
sales for large department stores in Hong Kong thanks to growing
consumer confidence.
</P>
<P>
Jusco Store (Hong Kong) Co. Limited, one of the largest
department stores in Hong Kong, today reported a double-digit
sales growth for the two weeks before the Lunar News Year's Day,
compared with the same period of 1995.
</P>
<P>
Jusco, a merchandise company funded by Japanese capital, saw
its four stores in Hong Kong record the highest sales on the New
Year's Eve. Fashion items and gifts were hot cakes during the
festive season, all posting a 30-percent rise in sales.
</P>
<P>
Yamaguchi, managing director of Jusco were optimistic about
Hong Kong's retail business in 1997 though not all retailers would
be able to capitalize on the recovery of consumer market.
</P>
<P>
In his view, consumers' desire to consume has restored in
anticipation of the smooth transition in mid 1997. The active
stock and property market and booming tourist industry helped to
build up people's confidence.
</P>
<P>
But some retailers would still face rising operation costs,
said Yamaguchi, who believed that value-for-money goods and
cost-effective measures were the key to success. 
</P>
</TEXT>
