<HEADLINE> Tianjin's Hi-Tech Sector Approaching Economies of Scale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The scale of production in the
high-tech sector of this, north China's largest port city, has
been significantly enlarged, according to the latest statistics.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 four group companies, with a total registered capital
of more than 400 billion yuan (approximately 50 million US
dollars) were established in the municipality's hi-tech industrial
park.
</P>
<P>
In addition, in the hi-tech park last year the sales of 22
types of products were reported at over 10 million yuan (about 1.2
million US dollars), much more than in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to officials at the hi-tech park, to date there are
altogether more than 2,700 enterprises located there, and most of
the products are competitive in the market.
</P>
<P>
"The development of the hi-tech sector in Tianjin will continue
to contribute in restructuring the economy, and as an increasing
number of hi-tech enterprises reach economies of scale, we will
have more confidence in the city's economic future," the officials
commented. 
</P>
