The minister refuted reports that the establishing of another
export processing zone in Port Harcourt in southern Rivers
State would adversely affect the operations of the Calabar zone.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two zones will complement each other as
Calabar will concentrate on manufacture and Port Harcourt on the
oil and gas industry.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Administrator of Cross Rivers State, Colonel
Umaru Ahmed, has expressed disappointment over the lukewarm
attitudes of local manufacturers to the Calabar Export Processing
Zone, urging them to invest more in the zone. 
