<HEADLINE> Spanish Royal Couple to Visit Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Spanish King Juan Carlos and
Queen Sophia is scheduled to pay an official visit to Egypt on
February 17-20, their first in 20 years, to cement bilateral trade
links.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's MENA news agency today quoted Spain's Ambassador to
Egypt Juan Alfonso Ortiz as saying that the king will be
accompanied by a business delegation which groups 55 Spanish
businessmen and investors specializing in oil, contracting,
communications, electricity and power.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish monarch will hold talks with President Hosni
Mubarak next Tuesday on the Mideast peace process and Europe's
role in it as well as the bilateral economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish King will attend an economic symposium on the
expansion of trade exchange and joint investments in both
countries.
</P>
<P>
He will also meet Egyptian businessmen over a luncheon and
speak on economic and trade cooperation between the two countries
and boosting joint projects.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Spanish investors and businessmen will have
talks with their counterparts in Egypt on the possibility of
augmenting Egyptian exports to Spain and increasing Spanish
investments and joint projects.
</P>
<P>
The two sides signed an agreement on economic and industrial
cooperation in March 1991, agreement on investment protection and
an agreement to avoid dual taxation in November 1992.
</P>
<P>
The volume of two-way trade was at 796 million Egyptian pounds
(about 234 million U.S. dollars) in 1993, then rose to 988.9
million pounds (290.8 million dollars) in 1994 and took another
leap to hit 1.16 billion(341 million dollars) in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Egypt exported 533 million pounds(157 million dollars) of
commodities to Spain against 626 million pounds(184 million
dollars) of imports in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The main exports to Spain include oil and textiles, while the
imports are basically tires, spare parts, meat, filters and
telephone wires. 
</P>
