<HEADLINE> Further Cooperation in Macao is Best Souvenir: Chinese Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Further cooperation on the
question of Macao between China and Portugal is the best souvenir
to mark the 10th anniversary of the signing of the Sino-Portuguese
Joint Declaration, a top Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Wang Qiren, director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch,
made these remarks while addressing a gathering here marking the
Chinese Lunar New Year, which was attended by more than 1,000
Macao celebrities and officials of the Macao government.
</P>
<P>
"On the 10th anniversary of the signing of the Sino-Portuguese
Joint Declaration this year, the best souvenir would be
maintaining the good cooperation between China and Portugal so
that Macao's economy would keep growing, society remain in good
order and transitional affairs be completed in time," said Wang.
</P>
<P>
The director said that the three big issues of the transitional
affairs concerning civil servants, language and law have all
scored new progress, but further efforts still need to be made.
</P>
<P>
He urged all residents of Macao to take a more active part in
the transitional affairs, in Macao's economic growth and social
stability. He also urged the Macao government to take further
effective measures, pledging that the Chinese side would offer
whatever help it can.
</P>
<P>
China and Portugal have maintained good relations over the past
few years. Exchange of visits between state leaders has been
frequent. China's Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen
visited Portugal last month, and Portuguese President Jorge
Sampaio is to visit China this month.
</P>
<P>
"All questions concerning Macao's transition will be able to be
handled properly if both China and Portugal take into
consideration the general interests of a long-term friendship
between the two sides, and the overall and long-term interests of
Macao," Wang stressed.
</P>
<P>
Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira said in his speech that
multiple cooperation between the two sides has become an important
factor in promoting the process of Macao transitional affairs,
and that the Macao government is fully aware of that.
</P>
<P>
"The Government will do its best to promote the friendly
relationship between Portugal and China," he said, adding that the
Portuguese president's upcoming visit to China would further
enhance the existing relations of understanding.  
</P>
</TEXT>
