<HEADLINE> Macao Arsonists Burn 30 Motor Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Criminal gangs in Macao burnt a
total of 30 motor vehicles early Tuesday morning, and police
established a special team to investigate the case, according to
today's local newspaper the Macao Daily News.
</P>
<P>
Almost simultaneously at about 6 a.m. on Tuesday, motorcycles,
cars and trucks at four different sites in Macao were set on
fire. Sixteen motorcycles and a truck were seriously burnt, but no
one was hurt.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that one of the crime sites was only a dozen
meters away from the headquarters of the special anti-crime police
forces.
</P>
<P>
The arson attack is the latest in a string of bombings and
shootings, which have burnt dozens of motorcycles and cars over
the past several months.
</P>
<P>
The reason for arsons was unknown.
</P>
<P>
Police said that they suspect Tuesday's arsons may be committed
by one group of gangsters, and further investigations are being
made.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a police action coordination center was established
on Tuesday by several departments of local police, in a bid to
enhance exchange of information and to take quick joint actions
against crimes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
