<HEADLINE> HK Stock Trading Reaches Record High in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Turnover at the Stock
Exchange of Hong Kong surged by over 50 percent last month to hit
a record high of 214 billion HK dollars (27 billion U.S. dollars),
compared with the December figure.
</P>
<P>
Average daily turnover also climbed 40 percent to more than 11
billion HK dollars (1.4 billion U.S. dollars), compared with that
in December, according to the Stock Exchange's monthly market
statistics available today.
</P>
<P>
Last month, seven new companies were listed and three were
delisted, bringing the number of listed companies to 587.
</P>
<P>
Both All Ordinaries Index and Hang Seng Index moved up and down
during the month. However, their month-end closings were almost
unchanged compared with the previous month. 
