<HEADLINE> Macao Joins Five International Tourism Bodies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Macao has joined five
international tourism organizations, which would help Macao
cultivate its tourism and promote its fame across the world, a
local tourism official said.
</P>
<P>
The five bodies are the Asia-Pacific Tourism Association
(PATA), the World Tourism Organization (WTO), the East Asia
Tourism Association (EATA), the Asia Association of Convention and
Visitor Bureaux (AACVB) and the International Congress and
Conference Association (ICCA).
</P>
<P>
Joao Manuel Antunes, director of the Macao Tourism Department,
said on Tuesday that by joining those world bodies, Macao can get
a better publicity at a least expense.
</P>
<P>
"Each time Macao hosts an international conference
successfully, Macao improves its ability of organization," said
Antunes. "That also means a better chance of publicity and more
visitors' arrivals."
</P>
<P>
The Macao Tourism Department first joined the PATA in 1957, and
is currently member of the executive committee of the
organization. The PATA is composed mainly of tourism departments,
air companies, hotels and other tourism agencies in countries and
regions in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Macao was notified last week to become member of
the administrative council of the World Tourism Organization,
which now has 136 member tourism departments.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
