<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong '97 Stamp Exhibition Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong '97 Stamp
Exhibition, the size of which is equivalent to or even bigger than
world class ones, opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition
Center is also the first ever Asian international stamp exhibition
held in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong '97 aims to sustain the philatelic interest generated
in Hong Kong '94 and reinforce Hong Kong's position as one of the
world's major centers of philately, Postmaster General Robert
Footman, who is president of the event's organizing committee,
said at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Response to the five-day event is overwhelming, he said.
</P>
<P>
The venue occupies a floor area of about 18,000 square
meters. Over 200 sales booths are rented to stamp dealers, postal
administrations, scrutiny printers, philatelic publishers and
stationery suppliers.
</P>
<P>
In addition, there are more than 1,000 frames of treasured
exhibits on display.
</P>
<P>
At the Court of Honor, people are able to see some extremely
rare and valuable collections which include the world's earliest
recorded cover bearing a Penny Black, extracts from the Royal
Collection consisting of some very rare early Hong Kong postage
stamps and exhibits from the Netherlands Postal Museum and the
Hong Kong Museum of History.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is definitely a holiday for local stamps lovers,
some of whom queued for entry overnight.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Post Office, organizer of the exhibition, expects
the attendance to be very high.
</P>
<P>
For the event, it has issued Hong Kong '97 Definitive Stamp
Sheetlet Series No. 1, 2 and 3 and will issue No 4 and 5 of the
series and other products.
</P>
<P>
A special postmark is introduced to the exhibition, with a
different postmark for each of the five days.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
