<HEADLINE> Chinese Pro Basketball League to Start Play-offs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Jilin Tigers, who finished top
in the Chinese Professional Basketball League regular season, will
take on fourth placer Henan Wildcats in Changchun in its opener of
the semi-final play-offs on Friday, organizers said here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou Rams and Beijing Lions, who finished second and third
respectively in the 28-round regular season, will meet each other
in Guangzhou in the best-of-seven semi-finals.
</P>
