are confident to win the champion," said Sun Jun, on behalf of the
Tigers, who kept unbeaten for 14 games at home in the regular
season.
</P>
<P>
The Rams, on a 20-8 record for the playoffs, were the top
scoring team in the regular season by averaging 116 points per
game. They also lead the league in field goals, three pointers
and free throws.
</P>
<P>
The Lions entered the semi-finals with a 17-11 record and the
wildcats with 14-14. 
