<HEADLINE> IOC Will not Seek to Lengthen Downhill Course </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The International Olympic
Committee (IOC) announced on Wednesday that it will not push
Nagano organisers to lengthen the men's downhill course.
</P>
<P>
IOC director general Francois Carrard said: "We respect
totally the concerns for the local environment and the IOC is
never going to force anything upon Nagano Olympic Organising
Committee (NOOC)."
</P>
<P>
The International Ski Federation (FIS) requested the NOOC to
raise the start of the men's downhill to 1,800 meters above sea
level.
</P>
<P>
But the NOOC has refused the request, saying that a higher
start would encroach on an environmentally sensitive national
park. 
</P>
