denied the reports, saying South Africa's support for the Lesotho
government would be executed through diplomatic channels rather
than military means.
</P>
<P>
Mutinous junior officers of Lesotho's Police Training College
and representatives from 10 police districts in the country
surrounded Police Headquarters in Maseru last Thursday, and
forced Police Commissioner Bolutu Makoaba, his deputy and three
other senior officers to be dismissd. 
