embassies in Malaysia and Singapore to step up diplomatic
relations with ASEAN member countries in an effort to collaborate
with them in the region's economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Jamie Gama said efforts to forge closer relations with the
members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) --
Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand
and Vietnam, were long overdue.
</P>
<P>
"However, we're moving now with plans to open up our embassies
in Kuala Lumpur and Singapore later this year," he was quoted by
Malaysia's news agency Bernama as saying after visiting Portuguese
historic sites and the Portuguese Settlement in Melaka (Malacca),
about 145 kilometers south from here.
</P>
<P>
Portugal just opened its embassy in the Philippines this year,
the second diplomatic office in the region. It already has its
embassy in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Jamie, who flew in for a short visit on his way to Singapore to
attend the 12th ASEAN-European Union Ministerial Meeting there
Thursday, said Portugal hopes not only to improve economic and
business ties but also to forge closer political and cultural
links with ASEAN members.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that a high level visit to the region either by
Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio or Prime Minister Antonio
Guterres is also being scheduled later this year.  
