<HEADLINE> Tanzania To Launch Deep Water Research Ship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A Tanzanian institute
(TAFIRI) will launch a new deep water research ship next month
for establishing fish distribution on the Tanzanian side of Lake
Victoria, reports reaching here from Mwanza said today.
</P>
<P>
TAFIRI Director General, professor Phillipo Bwatondi said in
Mwanza on Tuesday that the research ship financed by the European
Community and build by Pasiansi Boat Yard Project would enable
the Tanzania Fisheries Research Institute (TAFIRI) to conduct
intensive research on fish stock distribution.
</P>
<P>
Bwatondi indicated that the vessel will be the first of its
kind to be introduced in Tanzania and is equipped with modern
echo sound system.
</P>
<P>
The director general added that the ship would help the
research institute to get correct data on the remaining fish
stock in Lake Victoria, especially at this time when fish
processors are keen to know the facts on Lake Victoria.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, the findings which would be obtained
by TAFIRI through using the vessel would help the government
decide whether it could license new fishing processing factory.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
