<HEADLINE> Vietnam Grants 34 Foreign Projects in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 12 (Xinhua) - Vietnam granted licenses to 34
foreign invested projects worth about 600 million U.S. dollars in
January this year.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-nine of the projects cover oil and gas exploration and
exploitation, light and heavy industry, construction of
infrastructure and real estate and five others involve tourism,
service, culture, health care and education, according to the
Ministry of Planning and Investment today.
</P>
<P>
By the end of January, Vietnam had had 1,583 foreign funded
projects operating with more than 27 billion dollars, providing
jobs for 150,000 workers.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is leading the 56 investor countries and regions with
150 projects valued at over 5 billion dollars. Taiwan ranks second
with 258 projects worth more than 3.8 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Ho Chi Minh City now has 492 foreign-invested projects valued
at 7.77 billion dollars followed by Hanoi with 259 such projects
worth more than 6.58 billion dollars. 
</P>
