<HEADLINE> Philippines to Rid Metro Manila of Street Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos set in motion here today an innovative campaign to rid Metro
Manila of street children by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The president approved the release of 8 million pesos (305,343
U.S. dollars) to provide street children with proper education,
livelihood opportunities and capability building assistance.
</P>
<P>
The task will be implemented and coordinated by the Special
Unit for Street Children the president created last month in the
Department of Social Welfare.
</P>
<P>
The campaign, called "Zero Street Children for Philippines
2000", targets 5,131 street kids and their families, and will
involve not only government agencies but non-government
organizations as well.  
