<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mini-Baby Survives in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, February 12 (Xinhua) -- A premature baby girl born
after a gestation period of only 192 days and weighing just 950
grams at birth is in stable condition in a Shenzhen hospital.
</P>
<P>
Experts claim it is the first such case in the city, located in
south China's Guangdong Province, as most babies weighing below
1,500 grams do not have life-sustaining heart, liver and kidney
functions, according to the Shenzhen Special Zone Daily.
</P>
<P>
The child's mother did not expect her to survive, but 70 days
after the infant was brought to the local maternity and child care
hospital, she was taken off a respirator and can breathe on her
own and drink milk. She now weighs 1,500 grams.
</P>
<P>
Experts say her low weight is no longer
life-threatening. Before this, the hospital had treated several
babies weighing between 1,000 and 1,500 grams.  
</P>
</TEXT>
