to fight inside eastern Zaire, but Uganda has denied any
involvement.
</P>
<P>
Zairean rebels took up arms to fight the Kinshasa regime last
October and have occupied large tracts of territory in eastern
Zaire, and earlier this month Kinshasa launched a
counter-offensive and intense fighting is going on there.
</P>
<P>
Uganda supports non-violent political solutions to the
existing problems in Zaire, Kadaga noted.
</P>
<P>
Although Uganda is not involved in Zairean affairs, Zaire has
been harboring rebels fighting Uganda for several years, the
state minister counter-charged.
</P>
<P>
''The Uganda government take this opportunity to urge all
governments in the region to respect and adhere to Organization
of Africa Unity charter on human and people rights and other
international conventions relating to the rights of citizenship
and nationality,'' she said. 
