<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slovakia Records Trade Deficit in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia ran a trade deficit of
2.15 billion U.S. dollars in 1996 as against a surplus of 56.7
million dollars recorded in 1995 and 109 million dollars in 1994,
according to the latest report of the National Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The exports in 1996 amounted to 9.02 billion dollars, an
increase of six percent, while the imports totalled 11.17 billion
dollars, a sharp increase of 28.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Experts attributed the deficit mainly to lack of
competitiveness of the country's high value-added goods in the
world market and insufficient channels of exports.
</P>
<P>
About 85 percent of Slovakia's exports have been carried out
through the Czech Republic since the two separated from each other
in January 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
