<HEADLINE> Electronics Industry in Shenzhen Moves in High Gear </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The electronics industry in
the Special Economic Zone of Shenzhen in south China's Guangdong
Province turned out 50 billion yuan in electronics products in
1996, accounting for half of the city's total industrial output
value.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen's electronics industry, with a 30 percent increase in
output value last year, has become a leader in China in the sector.
</P>
<P>
The output value of personal computers, program-controlled
switches, fiber cables and mobile phones topped 20 billion yuan,
up 80 percent over the previous year. These hi-tech sectors have
become the backbones of the city's electronics industry.
</P>
<P>
Also, the city's production of color TV sets and electronics
elements grew rapidly in 1996, up 30 percent and 15 percent
respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
