<HEADLINE> Shaanxi's Foreign Trade Hits New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi
Province made 1.75 billion US dollars in foreign trade volume in
1996, a growth of four percent over the same period in the
previous year and standing above the national average.
</P>
<P>
According to the local customs office, Shaanxi exported 1.09
billion US dollars worth of products, while imports topped 660
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Major export products in the northwestern Chinese province
include goods from the machinery and electronics sectors, followed
by textiles and chemical industrial materials.
</P>
<P>
Provincial sources said the state-owned enterprises still
dominated Shaanxi's foreign trade with 1.39 billion US dollars in
import and export volume, or 79 percent of the total foreign trade
volume.
</P>
<P>
Additionally, overseas-funded enterprises made 360 million US
dollars in import and expert volume in 1996, an increase of 74
percent.  
</P>
