<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man Killing Six in New Zealand Facing 15 Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The man who killed six
people in New Zealand's central North Island last Saturday
appeared in court today, facing 15 charges.
</P>
<P>
Stephen Anderson, who shot dead people including his father in
the small town of Raurimu on central North Island, now faces six
counts of murder, eight counts of attempted murder and illegal
possession of a gun. He appeared today at Hamilton District Court
about 150 km south of Auckland, the largest city in New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
He will be remanded in a mental hospital for the next two
weeks for further psychiatric assessment.
</P>
<P>
A memorial service was held in Raurimu this morning for the
victims of Saturday's massacre.
</P>
<P>
About 400 people attended the service, including Governor
General Sir Michael Hardie Boys, Prime Minister Jim Bolger and
relatives of the dead.  
</P>
</TEXT>
