<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Population Grows 2% in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's population reached 76
million by the end of 1996, with an annual growth rate of 2.0
percent, official statistics showed.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics published in today's Vietnamese Daily
Nhan Dan, the average family size reduced from 3.3 children per
family in 1994 to 2.78 in 1996. At the same time, the birth rate
fell to an estimated 2.1 percent in 1996 compared to 2.39 percent
in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's population was estimated at 23 million in 1945, it
expanded to 30.2 million in 1960.
</P>
<P>
Despite the government's policy of family planning and
population control since the early 1960's, Vietnam is still under
increasing pressure of population growth.
</P>
<P>
At the present birth rate, which means three babies every
minute, Vietnam is growing by a village a day, a new district a
month, and a new province a year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese population experts estimated that the country's
population will reach 82 million in 2000, and 135-140 million by
the middle of 21st century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
