<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Urges People to Be More Fire-conscious </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria's fire fighting
authorities urged people to pay much more attention to forest
fires after 3,030 blazes destroyed 1,200 hectares of mature forest
and 520 plants nurseries across the country last year.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that most of the fires were caused by farmers'
carelessness, burning grass on waste land or burning wheat stubble
for fertilizer near forests.
</P>
<P>
Some of the fires were caused by cigarette butts dropped
carelessly by forest guards or passers-by.
</P>
<P>
In the first month of this year alone, even with the mountains
covered by snow, five forest fires have been reported in the
country. 
</P>
