<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM to Attend OIC Summit in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina will be visiting Pakistan from March 20 to 23 to
attend the extraordinary summit of the Organization of Islamic
Conference (OIC), which will be held in connection with the
celebration of the independence of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The extraordinary conference of the OIC will be attended by
heads of government of all member countries.
</P>
<P>
Hasina would use the occasion to meet with the would-be prime
minister of Pakistan Nawaz Sharif, discussing the issues related
to repatriation of stranded Pakistanis and other outstanding
disputes, said the Foreign Ministry sources.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh has longtime demanded sharing the assets and
liabilities with Pakistan before they parted their ways in 1971
and the repatriation of tens of thousands of stranded Pakistanis
from Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Sheikh Hasina will also hold bilateral talks with
heads of other Muslim countries including Malaysia and Iran, said
the sources.
</P>
<P>
It is learnt that the agenda of this special OIC summit will be
the challenges before the Islamic countries in the 21st century.
</P>
