<HEADLINE> Task Force on Traffic Control to Be Set Up in Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The Delhi government has
decided to set up a special task force in a bid to improve the
present situation of traffic congestion, chaos and high rate of
accidents in the Indian capital, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The high-powered panel, which will be known as the Traffic
Management Task Force (TMTF), will formulate the policy on
vehicular movement in the city and oversee its implementation.
</P>
<P>
The TMTF would be a multidimensional body which would review in
detail various aspects of Delhi's traffic including the creation
of general awareness among people about traffic regulations,
effective enforcement of these rules and checking traffic
violations like rash driving by private buses.
</P>
<P>
Besides setting up the task force, the Delhi government will
take other measures to solve the traffic problems. Prominent among
these was the construction of an elevated highway above the entire
46-km length of the ring road around the capital, the same sources
added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
