<HEADLINE> Share Prices on Kuala Lumpur Stock Market Open Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange opened higher this morning, the first
trading day of the year of the Ox, after a long festive break.
</P>
<P>
At 12.30 hours today, the Composite Index added 15.31 points to
1,257.26, the Emas Index was at 360.82, up 4.62 points and the
Industrial Index was 2,355.01, up 24.21 points.
</P>
<P>
However, the second board index was 614.57 points, down 2.35
points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 226.348 million units valued at 1.067 billion
ringgit (about 426.8 million U.S. dollars) by the time.
</P>
<P>
The local market was aided by the strong overnight close on
Wall Street, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The firm undertone of the market before it closed for the long
Chinese New Year and Moslem's festival of Fast-breaking holidays
last week, coupled with the firmer ringgit, was also attributable
to the rise in share prices, they said.
</P>
<P>
"It was a good start to the week, as far as the share market
was concerned, but this is left to be seen for the rest of the
week, a dealer said.
</P>
<P>
"We expect players to come back into the market in full force
on Monday next week, as most were still away for the festive
break," another dealer said.  
</P>
