<DOCNO> XIE19970212.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar National Races Urged to Safeguard Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Senior-General
Than Shwe today urged all the national races in the country to
safeguard the Union and ensure its lasting existence with the
Union spirit.
</P>
<P>
In his message to today's Golden Jubilee Myanmar Union day,
Than Shwe, who is also chairman of the ruling State Law and Order
Restoration Council, called on the national races to oppose and
crush the internal and external "destructive elements" who are
"disturbing" and "disrupting" the stability and progress of the
state.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that "at present, neo-colonialists are found to
be blatantly interfering in the internal affairs of other
countries pursuing their policy of hegemony in various parts of
the world."
</P>
<P>
"Traitorous elements with negative views in the country, who
are cohorts of the colonialists, at the same time, are offering
their support to the neo-colonialists, to enable them to meddle in
the internal affairs of our country," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that national solidarity has been restored and
different groups of various national races have joined with the
Tatmadaw (Armed Forces) in their endeavors to implement regional
development projects.
</P>
<P>
He also urged all Myanmar national races to take part in
building a peaceful, modern and developed nation, while the
government is striving for the progress in economic and social
life of the people along with peace and tranquillity.
</P>
<P>
Fifty years ago on the very day in 1947 before Myanmar regained
independence from Britain, the then Myanmar leaders led by General
Aung San, national hero, and representatives of all the national
races met in Panglong and signed the Panglong Agreement to strive
for an end to the British colonialists' rule in the country and
formed the Union of Burma (Myanmar). One year later in January
1948, Myanmar regained independence.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a Union Flag hoisting ceremony was held at the
People's Square here this morning to mark the Golden Jubilee
Myanmar Union Day.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, there were Union Flag relay activities in the
capital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
