<HEADLINE> Izetbegovic, Tudjman Exchange Views on Mostar Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Croatian President Franjo
Tudjman and Alije Izetbegovic, Chairman of the three-man
Presidency of Bosnia, spoke by phone today about Monday's clash
between Croats and Muslims in Bosnia's divided city of Mostar.
</P>
<P>
According to information from the Croatian capital Zagreb,
Tudjman and Izetbegovic agreed that the cause and process of the
clash, in which three Muslims and two Croats died, should be
revealed to the public as soon as possible under the impartial
supervision of the international community.
</P>
<P>
Those who took part in the incidents and the political leaders
behind them should be punished by law, the two men agreed during
their conversation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
