<HEADLINE> Deng Yaping Enters Athlete Committee of IOC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 12 (Xinhua) -- China's world and Olympic
table tennis champion Deng Yaping was selected a member of the
Athlete Commission of the International Olympic Committee, the
Chinese Olympic Committee announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to Wei Jizhong, Secretary-General of the COC, this
decision was informed by IOC president Antonio Samaranch recently.
</P>
<P>
In the message addressed to Deng, Samaranch said:"I believe
 you can do excellent work in the Athlete Commission."
</P>
<P>
The Athlete Commission of IOC includes a total of 19
members. The former representative of China was Li Ning, who had
won 15 world men's gymnastic titles before he retired in 1988.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Deng is the most talented player in the table
tennis world. The Chinese has won four Olympic gold medals and 15
world titles during her career. She claimed the singles gold
following the doubles victory with teammate Qiao Hong in the
Atlanta Olympics last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
