<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka People's Alliance District MP Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 12 (Xinhua) -- Nalanda Ellawala, Sri Lanka's
ruling People's Alliance MP for Ratnapura district, was shot dead
on Tuesday evening at a bus stand in Kuruvita town, about 110
kilometers from Colombo, according to police sources here today.
</P>
<P>
An unidentified gunman shot at the vehicle in which Ellawala
was traveling with his bodyguard and several others, the sources
said, adding his bodyguard and five others were injured in the
incident.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that he was carrying with him the nomination
papers to be filed today for the local government elections, when
the shooting took place.
</P>
<P>
Police were investigating the case, but no arrest has been made
so far.
</P>
<P>
Ellawala was the People's Alliance legislator and the Secretary
 General of all Ceylon Organizer of the Sri Lankan Freedom Party.
</P>
<P>
The local government elections will be held on March 27. It is
the first test for President Chandrika Kumaratunga's government,
which ended 17 years of the United National Party rule by winning
general and presidential elections in 1994.  
</P>
</TEXT>
