<HEADLINE> Financial Sector Backs Hangzhou's Infrastructures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The banking sector in
Zhejiang province's capital city of Hangzhou last year granted its
strongest support to date for the building of the city's
transportation network, drinking water supply and sewer system.
</P>
<P>
City officials have so far channeled about 1.6 billion yuan
into 20 of the city's 31 key infrastructural projects.
</P>
<P>
The city branch of the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China
shouldered over 38 percent of the loans, which totalled 500
million yuan. The bank plans to back 13 key projects, including
the third bridge across the Qianjiang River and the city's outer
ring road.
</P>
<P>
The China Construction Bank's Hangzhou branch has extended over
25 percent of the total loan funding, mainly to help improve the
city's transport system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
