<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Depressed Italian Mother Sets Fire to Herself, Baby Daughter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, February 11 (Xinhua) -- A depressed 35-year-old Italian
woman set fire to herself in her car early this morning, killing
herself and her six-month-old daughter, police said.
</P>
<P>
Her three other young children, also in the car at the time,
escaped serious injury and were recovering from minor burns this
morning at a hospital in Sicily, said a report reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy of the woman, identified by police as Alfia Lo
Faro, took place just after midnight on the Catania-Messina
expressway running along Sicily's eastern coast line.
</P>
<P>
Police said Lo Faro was apparently suffering from depression
aggravated by her family's financial problems. She left home with
four children after fighting with her husband Salvatore Musumeci.
</P>
<P>
After stopping at a gas station to buy gasoline and then
driving for a dozen kilometers, Lo Faro pulled over to the side of
the expressway, doused herself in gasoline and set herself on fire.
</P>
<P>
Lo Faro and her baby daughter died in the blaze. But her
10-year-old daughter managed to pull her two younger siblings from
the car. 
</P>
</TEXT>
