<HEADLINE> Estonia Ties Scotland 0-0 in Replayed World Cup Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Estonia held Scotland to a 0-0
tie in a replayed World Cup qualifying game in Monte Carlo on
Tuesday, four months after it failed to show up for the game.
</P>
<P>
Scotland squandered several chances and Estonia goalkeeper Mart
Poom made a series of saves to keep the Group Four leader
goal-less at Monaco's Louis II Stadium.
</P>
<P>
The result will be a major disappointment for the Scots who
claimed all three points after the Estonians failed to appear for
the October 9 game in Tallinn. FIFA disagreed and ordered the
replay.
</P>
<P>
Instead, Scotland earned only one point for a total of eight
from four games, one more then Austria which has seven from
three. Scotland has six from four and Estonia and Belarus have
four.
</P>
<P>
The Estonians refused to show up for the Oct. 9 match after
FIFA ordered that the kickoff be moved up four hours because of
the lack of proper floodlights at the Kadriorg Stadium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
