<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Price Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, February 12 (Xinhua) -- The average price for OPEC's
basket of seven crudes went down to 22.07 U.S. dollars a barrel
last week, the Vienna-based OPEC Secretariat announced today.
</P>
<P>
The market price last week was 34 cents down from the average
of 22.41 dollars a barrel registered by the Organization of the
Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) in the previous week.
</P>
<P>
As warm weather started to return to Europe and North America,
the monthly average for oil from OPEC nations was 23.23 dollars a
barrel in January, down from 23.51 dollars a barrel in December.
</P>
<P>
OPEC's reference oil price is 21 dollars a barrel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
