<HEADLINE> U.S. Troops to Hold Maneuvers in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 11 (Xinhua) -- Pentagon on Tuesday
announced that some 1,200 U.S. Army troops have begun deploying to
Kuwait for a four-month military exercise.
</P>
<P>
The maneuvers are a follow-on to the "intrinsic action"
exercises that took place at the end of last year, Pentagon
spokesman Kenneth Bacon said.
</P>
<P>
The troops will make use of U.S. armored equipment that is
stored in Kuwait during their exercises, which will also include
maneuvers with Kuwaiti military forces, Bacon said.
</P>
<P>
While most of the troops are from Fort Hood, Texas, the
maneuvers will also include a headquarters unit from Fort
McPherson, Georgia, Bacon said. 
